137	   * doesn't reliably reach `MarginCompensation` — a ViewPlugin with no
138	   * decorations of its own, whose `docViewUpdate` hook only fires when
139	   * SOME decoration source's output actually differs (CM6's own doc
140	   * comment: "due to content, decoration, or viewport changes"). For a
141	   * note containing only widget-replaced atoms (table/callout/hr/html —
142	   * `computeMarkers` deliberately skips these; `computeDecorations` doesn't
143	   * read `markerVisibility` at all), changing the setting produces
144	   * byte-identical StateField output, so CM6 correctly sees no diff and
145	   * never re-fires `docViewUpdate` — confirmed live: a table-only note's
146	   * marker visibility silently failed to update until this fix.
147	   *
148	   * Toggling outline mode off then immediately back on (via the registry
149	   * directly, not `toggleMode` — no user-facing Notice for an internal
150	   * refresh) guarantees two GENUINELY different decoration outputs
151	   * (`Decoration.none` vs. the real thing) regardless of note content,
152	   * which CM6 always detects as a real change — reliably triggering
153	   * `docViewUpdate` twice, with the second pass reading the just-saved
154	   * setting. Both toggles are public-API-only (an `Editor.setCursor` per
155	   * step, same trick `refreshDecorations` already uses) — no private CM6
156	   * access, consistent with this project's own public-API-only bar.
157	   *
158	   * `app.workspace.updateOptions()` — Obsidian's public "editor-extension-
159	   * affecting settings changed" API, and the obvious-looking replacement —
160	   * was evaluated (hardening 5.3) and FAILS exactly the scenario this hack
161	   * exists for, so don't swap it back in: its reconfigure transaction does
162	   * re-run the decoration plugins, but on a note whose decoration output is
163	   * byte-identical across the setting change (the table-only case above)
164	   * CM6 correctly sees no decoration diff and never fires
165	   * `MarginCompensation.docViewUpdate`, so the widget-atom marker silently
166	   * keeps its stale visibility — confirmed empirically: the marker-
167	   * visibility e2e tests (52-block-markers-icons.e2e.ts, the table-only
168	   * 'with-children' case in particular) fail with `updateOptions()` in
169	   * place of this method and pass with it. obsidian-lapel's use of
170	   * `updateOptions()` works because lapel swaps its registered extension
171	   * array entry in place (a genuinely different extension → a real
172	   * reconfigure diff); our extension instance is unchanged and reads the
173	   * setting live, so there is no diff for CM6 to see. Those same e2e tests
